  "text": "Early methods for semantic segmentation generally rely on handcrafted features, such as [CITATION_1] . However, the performance of these methods is far from being satisfactory. During the past few years, with the significant development of deep learning [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] , Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNNs) [CITATION_4] have been successfully applied to semantic segmentation.",
